codex
I identified a narrow deterministic gap: citation slot parsing only accepts bare `U.S.C. <section>` forms, so variants like `U.S.C. §473a` / `U.S.C. §§ 81 to 92.` don’t emit typed citation slots. I’m going to extend the shared citation regex in both `decompiler.py` and `codec.py` to accept optional section markers (`§`, `§§`, `sec.`, `section`) without changing existing slot names, then add focused regression tests in `test_ir_decompiler_slots.py` and run that test module.
